(491,	1,	'2015-03-09 06:34:25',	'2015-03-09 06:34:25',	'Damien and Kristen\'s wedding proved that fairy tales do come true if you marry your best friend on one the world\'s most beautiful islands.\r\n\r\nLord Howe Island, a world heritage listed island, is a destination wedding paradise that really has to be seen to be believed. It’s like stepping into a postcard. The turquoise waters and sub-tropical landscape make it a photographer’s dream and the perfect location for couples to experience a more relaxed and unique wedding.\r\n\r\nKristen and Damien chose a unique spot to experience their \'First Look\', a secluded old cemetery nestled within the rainforest, which allowed them to privately connect and soak up the quiet surroundings and pose for a few intimate pictures before the ceremony at Lovers Lookout.\r\n\r\nI took some great fun photos at this wedding. From Kristen arriving at the ceremony with her maid of honour on a pair wicker chairs strapped to the back of a ute, to a bit of bridal party fun on the 8th Hole of the Lord Howe Island Golf Club before the reception.\r\n\r\nHave a look at some of the shots and this video on You Tube.\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jnVv4hoVj48&amp;amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;amp;noredirect=1',	'Lord Howe Island',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'lord-howe-island',	'',	'',	'2015-03-30 09:44:40',	'2015-03-30 09:44:40',	'',	0,	'http://samantha.bizcatalyst.com.au/?post_type=uxbarn_portfolio&#038;p=491',	3,	'uxbarn_portfolio',	'',	0),
(492,	1,	'2015-03-09 06:29:13',	'2015-03-09 06:29:13',	'[vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_gallery images=\"108,107\" type=\"flexslider_slide\" grid_style=\"circle\" img_size=\"full\" columns=\"col3\" onclick=\"link_image\" interval=\"10\" show_bullets=\"true\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][uxb_heading text=\"What is a Pre-Wedding Photo Shoot\" type=\"h2\" has_line=\"false\" icon_size=\"16\"][vc_column_text]An engagement session is merely a portrait session of you and your fiancé. It usually occurs any time after your engagement till a month before your wedding day.\r\n\r\nMany couples are anxious about spending time in front of a camera on their wedding day and this session allows you to relax in front of the camera.\r\n\r\nAn engagement session gives you a great opportunity to get some more casual, relaxed images of you and your partner. They can range from a short few hours and one location to an extended period with outfit changes and multiple locations.\r\n\r\nSome couples come to learn a few posing tips so that the photography session becomes more natural on the wedding day. Often on the Wedding day the images in the middle of the session are the best as couples have relaxed and start enjoying the process. The huge benefit of an Engagement session is you learn how to maximise your best features whilst minimising any problems areas, making your wedding day images fantastic.\r\n\r\nEngagement sessions are built into a number of our wedding collections or can be added onto our more basic packages.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][uxb_divider style=\"special\"][uxb_heading text=\"Questions you may have\" type=\"h3\" has_line=\"false\" icon_size=\"16\"][vc_accordion use_as=\"accordion\" collapsible=\"yes\" active_section=\"1\" expanded=\"true\"][vc_accordion_tab title=\"Normal Text\"][vc_column_text]Mauris mauris ante, blandit et