(109,	1,	'2015-03-04 03:25:43',	'2015-03-04 03:25:43',	'[vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_gallery images=\"108,107\" type=\"flexslider_slide\" grid_style=\"circle\" img_size=\"full\" columns=\"col3\" onclick=\"link_image\" interval=\"10\" show_bullets=\"true\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][uxb_heading text=\"What is a Pre-Wedding Photo Shoot\" type=\"h2\" has_line=\"false\" icon_size=\"16\"][vc_column_text]An engagement session is merely a portrait session of you and your fiancé. It usually occurs any time after your engagement till a month before your wedding day.\r\n\r\nMany couples are anxious about spending time in front of a camera on their wedding day and this session allows you to relax in front of the camera.\r\n\r\nAn engagement session gives you a great opportunity to get some more casual, relaxed images of you and your partner. They can range from a short few hours and one location to an extended period with outfit changes and multiple locations.\r\n\r\nSome couples come to learn a few posing tips so that the photography session becomes more natural on the wedding day. Often on the Wedding day the images in the middle of the session are the best as couples have relaxed and start enjoying the process. The huge benefit of an Engagement session is you learn how to maximise your best features whilst minimising any problems areas, making your wedding day images fantastic.\r\n\r\nEngagement sessions are built into a number of our wedding collections or can be added onto our more basic packages.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row]',	'Engagement',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'106-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-03-04 03:25:43',	'2015-03-04 03:25:43',	'',	106,	'http://samantha.bizcatalyst.com.au/106-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
