(246,	1,	'2015-03-05 05:21:19',	'2015-03-05 05:21:19',	'[vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text]Sydney is an ideal location for wedding photography. Narrowing it down to the top 10 locations is difficult due the quality of various sites available. So here are my top 10 locations for wedding photography in Sydney:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong> The Rocks</strong> - Plenty of beautiful stone buildings and also some great reflective surfaces.  Sometimes you manage to get a famous landmark in the backdrop. Avoiding the crowds in your images can be challenging.</li>\r\n	<li><strong> Harbour Foreshore near the Harbour Bridge</strong> - amazing backdrop with the Opera House and Harbour Bridge. Winds can cause some challenging conditions. Can be a great area to use during rainy days as under the Harbour Bridge affords plenty of protection for the entire bridal party and your photographer.</li>\r\n	<li><strong> Opera House</strong> – Best on a beautiful sunny day with blue skies, this iconic landmark can make for some dramatic shots. Lack of nearby parking and large crowds can make it sometimes a challenge. Definitely worthwhile persisting.</li>\r\n	<li><strong> La Perouse</strong> – The dramatic Bear Island and the connecting bridge affords some unique opportunities particularly around sunset. If the tides are favorable you can gain access around the rocks on Bear Island for some great images. Just watch out for the mosquitos, particularly in summer where you can be eaten alive by the hoards. Parking is usually very good.</li>\r\n	<li><strong> St Mary’s Cathedral</strong> – This dramatic church with its beautiful architecture can make for some beautiful outdoor photos. Just don’t climb the stairs or try to access the church with your photographer as you will be quickly escorted off the church grounds.</li>\r\n	<li><strong> NSW State Theatre</strong> – This location is ideal for night bridal portraits if your reception venue is nearby.</li>\r\n	<li><strong> Pitt St Mall area</strong> – The area around the Centrepoint Westfield building provides a number of shop fronts that provide some interesting lighting at night. Definitely another night portrait location if your reception venue is nearby.</li>\r\n	<li><strong> Woolloomooloo Wharf Area</strong> - Access to the water without all the crowds. Easy parking.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-225\" src=\"http://samantha.bizcatalyst.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Woolloomooloo-Wharf-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"Woolloomooloo Wharf\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></li>\r\n	<li><strong>The Domain</strong> - Tree lined walkways and easy access to the NSW Art Gallery steps.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-224\" src=\"http://samantha.bizcatalyst.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/The-Domain-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"The Domain\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Hyde Park</strong> - Tree lined walkways, city skyline and interesting street performers can make for some interesting photo opportunities.\r\n<a href=\"http://samantha.bizcatalyst.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Hyde-Park-.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-226\" src=\"http://samantha.bizcatalyst.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Hyde-Park--300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Hyde Park\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][uxb_divider style=\"special\"][vc_gallery images=\"229,230,231,232,233,234,235,236,237,238,239,240,242,243,244,245\" type=\"image_grid\" grid_style=\"square\" img_size=\"full\" columns=\"col4\" onclick=\"link_image\" interval=\"5\" show_bullets=\"true\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]',	'Top 10 Sydney Wedding Photo Locations',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'223-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-03-05 05:21:19',	'2015-03-05 05:21:19',	'',	223,	'http://samantha.bizcatalyst.com.au/223-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(247,	1,	'2015-03-06 09:42:02',	'2015-03-06 09:42:02',	'[vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text]Brad and Jacqui had their first date exactly 12 months before their wedding day. Yet after meeting them you would think they had know each other for years. When I asked the groom why she was \'the one\' he described someone that he could easily spend hours talking about anything and everything. Whilst not necessarily romantic in its wording, the huge smile that instantly appeared on his face spoke of his deep love for his bride. Then the moment that I look forward to the most at every wedding - the moment the groom sees his bride for the first time. Brad\'s pure joy at seeing Jacqui with her Dad walking down the aisle was truly memorable.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]',	'Brad & Jacqui\'s Wedding',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'brad-jacquis-wedding',	'',	'',	'2015-03-10 05:19:20',	'2015-03-10 05:19:20',	'',	0,	'http://samantha.bizcatalyst.com.au/?p=247',	5,	'post',	'',	0),
(248,	1,	'2015-03-06 09:48:11',	'2015-03-06 09:48:11',	'[vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text]<strong><em>Most professional wedding photographers in Sydney charge $2000 - $12000 per wedding. What are you getting for your money?</em></strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Time - The average wedding will take me 60 hours from start to finish. As a professional photographer that specialises in attention to detail I will spend a lot more time in editing to get a product that I am happy with. So where is the 60 hours?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Meeting the couple - I need to understand your family dynamics to ensure all the moments that are important to you are captured. Getting to know you as a couple is extremely important as it will allow me to work comfortably around you, your family and your friends on your special day. Nobody should be on a blind date with their photographer on their wedding day.</li>\r\n	<li>Equipment preparation - a few days before the wedding all equipment will be checked and packed. As a minimum this is what equipment I carry:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Nikon D4S</li>\r\n	<li>Nikon D3S</li>\r\n	<li>Nikon D800</li>\r\n	<li>Sony a7S</li>\r\n	<li>Nikon 14-24mm f2.8</li>\r\n	<li>Nikon 24-70mm f2.8</li>\r\n	<li>Nikon 70-200 f2.8</li>\r\n	<li>Nikon 85mm f1.4</li>\r\n	<li>Nikon 105mm Macro f2.8</li>\r\n	<li>Sony Zeiss 55mm f1.8</li>\r\n	<li>Nikon SB 910 x 2</li>\r\n	<li>Nikon SB 700</li>\r\n	<li>Selection of Lensbaby lenses</li>\r\n	<li>Selection of light modifiers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The big day - this will start with the groom and bride getting ready and may finish as late as the bride and groom departing the reception. During this time I will generally shoot about 3000 photographs. My aim is to capture the rare and spontaneous moments for you and your family. The time allocated to the formal wedding photographs may vary from 30mins - 2 hours.</li>\r\n	<li>Editing and processing - ever tried to sort through 3000 photographs? It takes time. After sorting images, they then are colour and tone corrected. Where required further enhancements are added to give that magic touch.</li>\r\n	<li>Artwork creation time - this is where I complete your wedding album or slideshow. Images are also prepared for you to share easily on social media. Any prints that you have requested undergo special colour checking and calibration with the printer and paper that is being used. This ensures that the images that you see on my computer match the photographs that I deliver to you.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Time to meet again - now you get to finally see some of your photographs and make a decision on the final product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n	<li>Cost of goods - Wedding albums are expensive to create - both from a time perspective and also from a cost of manufacture. Wholesale cost of wedding albums to the photographer usually range from $500 - $3000 and a top of the line wedding album can cost in excess of $5000. Those prices do not include the time that I have spent editing the photos and the considerable time that goes into the design of the wedding album design.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n	<li>Cost of equipment - Professional camera equipment is expensive. My current equipment retails at more than $60,000.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n	<li>Cost of running a business - Most reception venues in Australia require a photographer to be insured for 20 million dollars of liability insurance. Then there is the extra cost of insuring the camera equipment. Advertising, accounting, marketing, and general business expenses all add to the cost of running a business.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]',	'Ever Wondered Why It Costs So Much To Hire A Wedding Photographer?',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'ever-wondered-why-it-costs-so-much-to-hire-a-wedding-photographer',	'',	'',	'2015-03-10 05:18:28',	'2015-03-10 05:18:28',	'',	0,	'http://samantha.bizcatalyst.com.au/?p=248',	4,	'post',	'',	0),
